OL,4,Cover RAAC concerns
OL,6,FRAAC is a lightweight material used
OL,7,Fmostly in flat roofing but also in
OL,8,Ffloors and walls, between the 1950s
OL,9,Fand 1990s. It is cheaper than standard
OL,10,Fconcrete and has a lifespan of about
OL,11,F30 years.
OL,13,FSo far around 40 Scottish schools have
OL,14,Fbeen found to have it.
OL,16,FInspections at Gatehouse revealed the
OL,17,Fpresence of panels classed as being at
OL,18,F"critical risk" level.
